cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.COM 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the performance evaluation of heterogeneous networks composed of macrocells and picocells. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper uses stochastic geometry and higher-order statistics to model network deployments and characterize the probability distribution of received power and aggregate interference. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper discusses self-organizing solutions to improve coverage, cell-edge throughput, and overall system capacity. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper considers the impact of interference on the average channel capacity of the network. 
5. cs.COM (Computers and Society) is the least likely category as the paper does not focus on social or ethical issues related to computer systems.
